1
00:01:46,958 --> 00:01:48,125
Stupid jerk!

2
00:01:48,208 --> 00:01:50,833
That was
my bestie's subordinate!

3
00:02:01,083 --> 00:02:03,708
[grunting]

4
00:02:03,791 --> 00:02:06,375
[PHOBIO]
Damn it! She'll pay for that.

5
00:02:08,166 --> 00:02:10,708
She should know
who she's messing with.

6
00:02:10,791 --> 00:02:12,958
I'm Phobio,
the Black Leopard Fang.

7
00:02:13,041 --> 00:02:15,083
There's not much we can
possibly do

8
00:02:15,166 --> 00:02:17,291
with Demon Lord Milim
in the picture.

9
00:02:17,375 --> 00:02:19,625
Even if Demon Lord Carrion
does command it.

10
00:02:19,708 --> 00:02:21,333
Shut up!

11
00:02:21,416 --> 00:02:24,458
Demon Lord Carrion wouldn't have
got his ass kicked like a loser.

12
00:02:24,541 --> 00:02:26,875
The hard truth is
that I just wasn't good enough.

13
00:02:27,875 --> 00:02:30,625
And my pride won't let me
go back empty-handed.

14
00:02:30,708 --> 00:02:32,708
So now I don't know what to do.

15
00:02:34,166 --> 00:02:35,625
You saw it.

16
00:02:35,708 --> 00:02:38,166
Those guys built a thriving town
all on their own.

17
00:02:38,250 --> 00:02:41,541
I treated them as if they were
just lowly monsters,

18
00:02:41,625 --> 00:02:43,250
but they have skills
and techniques

19
00:02:43,333 --> 00:02:44,958
that even we lack.

20
00:02:45,041 --> 00:02:46,458
It's true.

21
00:02:46,541 --> 00:02:48,833
Instead of ordering them
to serve us,

22
00:02:48,916 --> 00:02:50,708
I would have liked to have tried
and establish

23
00:02:50,791 --> 00:02:52,458
diplomatic relations with them.

24
00:02:52,541 --> 00:02:53,916
Agreed.

25
00:02:54,000 --> 00:02:56,458
Even if Lady Milim
hadn't stepped in,

26
00:02:56,541 --> 00:02:59,208
I still handled that thing
all wrong.

27
00:02:59,291 --> 00:03:00,916
I'll never gain their trust.

28
00:03:01,000 --> 00:03:03,875
Not when I tried to take over
without giving them a say.

29
00:03:04,916 --> 00:03:06,500
Not that it matters now.

30
00:03:06,583 --> 00:03:08,333
My wounds may have healed,

31
00:03:08,416 --> 00:03:10,583
but I'll never recover
from that humiliation.

32
00:03:10,666 --> 00:03:13,291
I have to find a way
to get revenge on her somehow,

33
00:03:13,375 --> 00:03:14,875
that way I don't cause
any more trouble

34
00:03:14,958 --> 00:03:16,583
for Lord Carrion.

35
00:03:16,666 --> 00:03:20,416
Sure, all that's easy to say,
but it's not exactly realistic.

36
00:03:20,500 --> 00:03:21,958
I already know!

37
00:03:22,041 --> 00:03:23,583
I don't need your stupid advice.

38
00:03:25,041 --> 00:03:28,583
Lookit, I'm just really
frustrated right now.

39
00:03:28,666 --> 00:03:30,125
[grunting]

40
00:03:30,208 --> 00:03:32,500
[MAN guffawing]

41
00:03:32,583 --> 00:03:33,916
Who goes there?

42
00:03:34,000 --> 00:03:36,541
♪

43
00:03:40,458 --> 00:03:42,708
[CLOWN]
I do understand how you feel.

44
00:03:42,791 --> 00:03:47,750
It must be very frustrating
to be so utterly frustrated.

45
00:03:47,833 --> 00:03:49,375
Greetings, fine people.

46
00:03:49,458 --> 00:03:52,375
I'm Footman, and it's a pleasure
to meet you.

47
00:03:52,458 --> 00:03:54,000
Footman?

48
00:03:54,083 --> 00:03:56,125
[FOOTMAN]
I'm a member of the esteemed

49
00:03:56,208 --> 00:03:57,708
Moderate Harlequin Alliance,

50
00:03:57,791 --> 00:04:01,000
the one known as
Footman, the Angry Pierrot.

51
00:04:01,083 --> 00:04:02,708
Please hold your applause.

52
00:04:02,791 --> 00:04:04,291
[PHOBIO groans]

53
00:04:04,375 --> 00:04:07,000
[TEAR] There's no need for
all those suspicious groans.

54
00:04:07,083 --> 00:04:08,583
I'm Tear.

55
00:04:08,666 --> 00:04:10,291
Don't worry,
we're friendly clowns.

56
00:04:10,375 --> 00:04:11,208
[FOOTMAN]
Mm-hmm.

57
00:04:11,291 --> 00:04:13,041
What do you want?

58
00:04:13,125 --> 00:04:14,666
[FOOTMAN laughs]

59
00:04:14,750 --> 00:04:16,208
[FOOTMAN]
If you must know,

60
00:04:16,291 --> 00:04:17,333
I was summoned here

61
00:04:17,416 --> 00:04:19,375
by all the angry
and hateful vibes

62
00:04:19,458 --> 00:04:20,583
you're giving off.

63
00:04:20,666 --> 00:04:22,750
[PHOBIO]
What's that supposed to mean?

64
00:04:22,833 --> 00:04:24,541
[FOOTMAN]
I'm saying I was drawn here

65
00:04:24,625 --> 00:04:26,166
by your feelings of rage.

66
00:04:26,250 --> 00:04:27,708
[PHOBIO gasps]

67
00:04:27,791 --> 00:04:29,958
[FOOTMAN] Why don't you tell me
what has angered you so?

68
00:04:30,041 --> 00:04:31,583
I'd love to hear it.

69
00:04:32,666 --> 00:04:35,875
I'm quite certain I could be
of assistance to you.

70
00:04:35,958 --> 00:04:37,875
[PHOBIO exhales]

71
00:04:37,958 --> 00:04:39,666
Ignore them.

72
00:04:39,750 --> 00:04:41,833
You don't have to answer
to these ridiculous clowns,

73
00:04:41,916 --> 00:04:43,083
Sir Phobio.

74
00:04:43,166 --> 00:04:44,583
Would you like me
to dispose of them?

75
00:04:46,000 --> 00:04:48,083
We are the Beastketeers
who proudly serve

76
00:04:48,166 --> 00:04:49,750
under Demon Lord Carrion.

77
00:04:49,833 --> 00:04:51,708
A couple of wandering majin
like yourselves

78
00:04:51,791 --> 00:04:53,375
are no match for us.

79
00:04:53,458 --> 00:04:55,500
[FOOTMAN]
You desire power, do you not?

80
00:04:55,583 --> 00:04:57,250
We have that in spades.

81
00:04:57,333 --> 00:05:00,250
More than
you've ever seen before.

82
00:05:00,333 --> 00:05:02,708
However, it comes
with great risk.

83
00:05:02,791 --> 00:05:06,125
Should you not be scared
by that teensy little detail.

84
00:05:06,208 --> 00:05:09,958
The power you stand to gain
is unfathomable.

85
00:05:10,041 --> 00:05:10,916
Really?

86
00:05:11,000 --> 00:05:12,541
My Lord.

87
00:05:12,625 --> 00:05:15,125
[TEAR] If you wanna defeat
that mean ol' Demon Lord Milim,

88
00:05:15,208 --> 00:05:19,041
then all you gotta do is become
a real Demon Lord yourself.

89
00:05:19,125 --> 00:05:21,458
[gasps]
What?

90
00:05:26,750 --> 00:05:28,125
Seriously?

91
00:05:28,208 --> 00:05:30,000
Do you actually think
you can fool me

92
00:05:30,083 --> 00:05:31,208
with that kind of nonsense?

93
00:05:31,291 --> 00:05:32,958
-[FOOTMAN] Charybdis.
-[PHOBIO gasps]

94
00:05:33,041 --> 00:05:35,083
♪

95
00:05:37,125 --> 00:05:39,250
[FOOTMAN]
Does it ring any bells?

96
00:05:39,333 --> 00:05:40,875
The Charybdis?

97
00:05:40,958 --> 00:05:41,833
Really?

98
00:05:41,916 --> 00:05:43,583
[ENRIO gasps]

99
00:05:43,666 --> 00:05:45,291
[TEAR]
Uh-huh.

100
00:05:45,375 --> 00:05:47,750
If you could harness the power
of the giant whale fish thing,

101
00:05:47,833 --> 00:05:50,333
then you'd be as powerful
as the Demon Lord.

102
00:05:50,416 --> 00:05:52,958
But if you're not interested,
we can always find someone else.

103
00:05:54,833 --> 00:05:56,333
Let's go, Footman.

104
00:05:56,416 --> 00:05:58,208
[FOOTMAN]
Mm-hmm-hmm.

105
00:05:58,291 --> 00:05:59,375
What a shame.

106
00:05:59,458 --> 00:06:00,458
Hold on.

107
00:06:00,541 --> 00:06:02,416
[BOTH]
Hmm?

108
00:06:02,500 --> 00:06:05,083
Don't do this. It's madness.

109
00:06:05,166 --> 00:06:08,083
[PHOBIO] Listen, I haven't liked
any of this from the start.

110
00:06:08,166 --> 00:06:09,916
Like, why did a fat, useless orc

111
00:06:10,000 --> 00:06:12,166
get chosen to be
the next Demon Lord?

112
00:06:12,250 --> 00:06:13,958
It's not fair!

113
00:06:14,041 --> 00:06:15,541
If they needed
a new Demon Lord,

114
00:06:15,625 --> 00:06:17,541
then why didn't
they choose me?!

115
00:06:17,625 --> 00:06:19,208
But if I were to get stronger,

116
00:06:19,291 --> 00:06:22,250
even Lord Carrion would have
no choice but to forgive me.

117
00:06:22,333 --> 00:06:23,916
Sir Phobio.

118
00:06:24,000 --> 00:06:25,375
I want to know more.

119
00:06:25,458 --> 00:06:28,625
[FOOTMAN] Ah.
A very wise move, Sir Phobio.

120
00:06:28,708 --> 00:06:30,250
Not that I'm surprised.

121
00:06:30,333 --> 00:06:32,041
It's obvious you possess
the talents

122
00:06:32,125 --> 00:06:33,500
to become a Demon Lord.

123
00:06:33,583 --> 00:06:35,708
[TEAR] It's not fair
that someone weaker than you

124
00:06:35,791 --> 00:06:37,833
got a shot at being
a Demon Lord first.

125
00:06:37,916 --> 00:06:39,333
I'm with you on that.

126
00:06:39,416 --> 00:06:41,666
Especially when you're
the best person for the job.

127
00:06:43,583 --> 00:06:45,500
[ENRIO]
Hmm.

128
00:06:45,583 --> 00:06:46,791
So tell me,

129
00:06:46,875 --> 00:06:49,166
what do you stand to gain
from all this?

130
00:06:49,250 --> 00:06:50,875
What are you after?

131
00:06:50,958 --> 00:06:52,666
[TEAR] Oh, we just want
special treatment

132
00:06:52,750 --> 00:06:54,416
once you become a Demon Lord.

133
00:06:54,500 --> 00:06:57,333
And, you know, maybe you could
do us a couple of small favors.

134
00:06:57,416 --> 00:06:58,916
[FOOTMAN laughs]

135
00:06:59,000 --> 00:07:01,333
Besides, it's not
as if we're capable

136
00:07:01,416 --> 00:07:03,500
of subduing Charybdis
on our own.

137
00:07:03,583 --> 00:07:05,291
[TEAR]
We did happen to find the place

138
00:07:05,375 --> 00:07:06,791
where it's sealed away,

139
00:07:06,875 --> 00:07:08,916
but without help, we're just
sitting on a gold mine.

140
00:07:09,000 --> 00:07:10,458
[FOOTMAN] But then
we happened to find you,

141
00:07:10,541 --> 00:07:12,125
so perfect timing, right?

142
00:07:13,125 --> 00:07:14,583
Yeah, maybe.

143
00:07:14,666 --> 00:07:17,000
Still though, we don't even know
if I'll have the ability

144
00:07:17,083 --> 00:07:18,833
to control Charybdis
in the first place.

145
00:07:18,916 --> 00:07:20,458
[FOOTMAN]
Ho-ho-ho.

146
00:07:20,541 --> 00:07:23,833
Don't be so modest,
if anyone can do it, you can!

147
00:07:23,916 --> 00:07:25,333
[TEAR]
You'll be fantastic.

148
00:07:26,458 --> 00:07:28,333
[PHOBIO]
So in exchange for their help,

149
00:07:28,416 --> 00:07:30,041
all they want are a few favors

150
00:07:30,125 --> 00:07:32,208
and the credit
for helping me reach the top?

151
00:07:35,125 --> 00:07:36,625
All right, then.

152
00:07:36,708 --> 00:07:38,458
I accept your offer.

153
00:07:38,541 --> 00:07:40,833
♪

154
00:07:43,416 --> 00:07:44,625
[PHOBIO]
Go back without me.

155
00:07:44,708 --> 00:07:45,875
Don't do this.

156
00:07:45,958 --> 00:07:48,000
Report on everything
that has happened.

157
00:07:48,083 --> 00:07:49,416
But, sir...

158
00:07:49,500 --> 00:07:52,416
I cannot cause more trouble
for Lord Carrion.

159
00:07:52,500 --> 00:07:54,208
So tell him that I'm resigning.

160
00:07:54,291 --> 00:07:56,333
I'm no longer a part
of the Beastketeers.

161
00:07:57,375 --> 00:08:00,000
Thank you for everything
you've done, Enrio.

162
00:08:00,083 --> 00:08:01,541
[ENRIO]
Sir Phobio.

163
00:08:01,625 --> 00:08:03,625
I will become stronger.

164
00:08:03,708 --> 00:08:05,375
Then Demon Lord Milim
will suffer

165
00:08:05,458 --> 00:08:06,791
under the wrath of my power.

166
00:08:06,875 --> 00:08:07,708
[ENRIO gasps]

167
00:08:08,916 --> 00:08:10,250
As you wish.

168
00:08:10,333 --> 00:08:12,666
I'll report to Lord Carrion.

169
00:08:12,750 --> 00:08:16,416
I warn you, the extent of
Charybdis' power is unknown.

170
00:08:16,500 --> 00:08:18,791
So please be careful, sir.

171
00:08:18,875 --> 00:08:21,041
♪

172
00:08:27,958 --> 00:08:30,625
[ENRIO] Sir Phobio is a not
a foolish man.

173
00:08:30,708 --> 00:08:34,083
If what they say is true,
and Charybdis does exist,

174
00:08:34,166 --> 00:08:36,583
I'm certain he'll find a way
to control it.

175
00:08:40,666 --> 00:08:42,791
[FOOTMAN]
Come. We have much to do.

176
00:08:42,875 --> 00:08:44,333
Yeah.

177
00:08:44,416 --> 00:08:47,583
The sooner I can combine
my power with Charybdis,

178
00:08:47,666 --> 00:08:50,125
the sooner I can make
Demon Lord Milim pay.

179
00:08:50,208 --> 00:08:52,166
I'll wipe that smug look
off her face.

180
00:08:52,250 --> 00:08:54,541
[FOOTMAN laughs]
That's the spirit.

181
00:08:54,625 --> 00:08:57,458
[TEAR] Uh-huh.
We'll be cheerin' for ya.

182
00:08:59,541 --> 00:09:00,416
[indistinct chatter]

183
00:09:04,208 --> 00:09:07,416
[ALL gasp]

184
00:09:09,291 --> 00:09:11,458
There, you see?
I told you I'd win.

185
00:09:11,541 --> 00:09:13,250
Looks like I'm the
stay-under-water

186
00:09:13,333 --> 00:09:14,458
breath-holding champion.

187
00:09:14,541 --> 00:09:16,750
Sorry, but I was
the winner here.

188
00:09:16,833 --> 00:09:18,041
You were?

189
00:09:18,125 --> 00:09:19,666
But I was the last one up.

190
00:09:19,750 --> 00:09:20,916
By a few seconds.

191
00:09:21,000 --> 00:09:23,291
You guys are acting
like sore losers.

192
00:09:23,375 --> 00:09:24,833
Shion. Shuna.

193
00:09:24,916 --> 00:09:27,166
Okay. We'll do another round.

194
00:09:27,250 --> 00:09:28,333
Let's settle the score.

195
00:09:28,416 --> 00:09:29,541
Very well.

196
00:09:29,625 --> 00:09:31,041
It's on.

197
00:09:31,125 --> 00:09:33,041
It's not a good idea to stay
underwater in the bath,

198
00:09:33,125 --> 00:09:35,000
but one more time
shouldn't hurt.

199
00:09:35,083 --> 00:09:35,916
[ALL]
Ready?

200
00:09:36,000 --> 00:09:36,875
[ALL inhale]

201
00:09:37,916 --> 00:09:41,166
[RIMURU] Aw.
Sounds like they're having fun.

202
00:09:41,250 --> 00:09:43,875
Kinda wish I had bathed
on that side.

203
00:09:43,958 --> 00:09:46,000
Over here there's just...

204
00:09:46,083 --> 00:09:47,208
an old dude.

205
00:09:48,833 --> 00:09:51,833
Hey, how long are you planning
on hanging around?

206
00:09:51,916 --> 00:09:54,833
Do you still think
we're like evil or whatever?

207
00:09:54,916 --> 00:09:57,375
Huh? No, I don't.

208
00:09:57,458 --> 00:09:58,916
To be completely honest,

209
00:09:59,000 --> 00:10:01,208
I stopped being suspicious
of you guys a while back.

210
00:10:01,291 --> 00:10:02,916
[RIMURU]
Then why haven't you left?

211
00:10:03,000 --> 00:10:06,125
Because this town you've built
is pretty relaxing,

212
00:10:06,208 --> 00:10:07,500
all things considered.

213
00:10:07,583 --> 00:10:10,458
I can't remember the last time
I took a break.

214
00:10:10,541 --> 00:10:13,541
So I thought I'd take this
opportunity to slow down a bit.

215
00:10:13,625 --> 00:10:15,541
[RIMURU]
Seriously?

216
00:10:15,625 --> 00:10:18,333
What happened to the whole
"I will see for myself

217
00:10:18,416 --> 00:10:22,583
whether or not you're truly
an ally of humans" spiel?

218
00:10:22,666 --> 00:10:24,958
For a second there,
you sounded pretty cool.

219
00:10:25,041 --> 00:10:26,083
[FUZE sighs]

220
00:10:26,166 --> 00:10:27,208
[RIMURU]
He's not even listening?!

221
00:10:27,291 --> 00:10:29,208
-Hey!
-[FUZE] Hmm?

222
00:10:29,291 --> 00:10:31,833
[RIMURU] What's the status on
Youm and his group?

223
00:10:31,916 --> 00:10:34,666
You promised to help us
make them look like champions,

224
00:10:34,750 --> 00:10:36,458
or is that part
of your brain on break, too?

225
00:10:36,541 --> 00:10:37,958
Ha, ha.

226
00:10:38,041 --> 00:10:40,000
[RIMURU]
"Ha, ha" isn't answer!

227
00:10:40,083 --> 00:10:41,916
I bet you don't even know
they left.

228
00:10:42,000 --> 00:10:44,083
They rode off to build
their reputation,

229
00:10:44,166 --> 00:10:45,541
lookin' fly as hell.

230
00:10:45,625 --> 00:10:47,916
You really should relax
a little bit.

231
00:10:48,000 --> 00:10:50,750
Besides, I've already finished
setting things up.

232
00:10:50,833 --> 00:10:51,666
[RIMURU]
You have?

233
00:10:51,750 --> 00:10:53,166
[FUZE]
Yes.

234
00:10:53,250 --> 00:10:54,958
Believe it or not, I've already
done the ground work

235
00:10:55,041 --> 00:10:57,083
for spreading the rumors
that they're the champions

236
00:10:57,166 --> 00:10:58,916
who defeated the Orc Lord.

237
00:10:59,000 --> 00:11:01,500
Of course, I was sure
to include all the details.

238
00:11:01,583 --> 00:11:03,000
Like how you and your people
are nothing,

239
00:11:03,083 --> 00:11:04,458
but a friendly town of monsters

240
00:11:04,541 --> 00:11:06,416
who gave them supplies
for their quest.

241
00:11:07,666 --> 00:11:09,041
[RIMURU]
Oh.

242
00:11:09,125 --> 00:11:10,708
Awesome sauce.

243
00:11:10,791 --> 00:11:12,541
It looks like he's slacking off,

244
00:11:12,625 --> 00:11:14,750
but he's actually ahead
of the game.

245
00:11:14,833 --> 00:11:17,083
[FUZE] Well, I think
I've soaked enough.

246
00:11:17,166 --> 00:11:18,708
[RIMURU]
Before I forget,

247
00:11:18,791 --> 00:11:20,958
I wanted to mention that
I'm thinking of building a road

248
00:11:21,041 --> 00:11:23,000
from our town
to the Kingdom of Blumund.

249
00:11:23,083 --> 00:11:26,416
[gasps]
Wait. What? Seriously?

250
00:11:26,500 --> 00:11:28,750
Uh, look,
I think it's a fine idea.

251
00:11:28,833 --> 00:11:31,083
But we're talking about
a national undertaking here.

252
00:11:31,166 --> 00:11:33,166
Think of how much it would cost.

253
00:11:33,250 --> 00:11:34,416
[RIMURU]
Chill out, Fuze, my boy.

254
00:11:34,500 --> 00:11:36,291
"Your boy?"

255
00:11:36,375 --> 00:11:38,416
Having you call me
that sounds weird.

256
00:11:38,500 --> 00:11:40,791
I mean, I'm not even sure
how old you really are.

257
00:11:40,875 --> 00:11:43,750
[RIMURU]
Meh, details schmetails.

258
00:11:43,833 --> 00:11:47,125
Having a road would make it
easier for us to do business.

259
00:11:47,208 --> 00:11:51,416
My people can handle paving it
and all the physical work.

260
00:11:51,500 --> 00:11:52,541
However...

261
00:11:52,625 --> 00:11:54,166
However?

262
00:11:54,250 --> 00:11:56,875
[RIMURU] I'd like to sell
some of our specially made goods

263
00:11:56,958 --> 00:11:58,208
to other countries.

264
00:11:58,291 --> 00:12:00,000
So, I was hoping
that you could introduce me

265
00:12:00,083 --> 00:12:01,583
to someone who can
give me some advice.

266
00:12:01,666 --> 00:12:03,125
Is that all?

267
00:12:03,208 --> 00:12:04,875
That sounds simple enough.

268
00:12:04,958 --> 00:12:06,083
[RIMURU]
Sweetness.

269
00:12:06,166 --> 00:12:07,291
[GIRLS giggling]

270
00:12:07,375 --> 00:12:08,833
-[RIMURU] Huh?
-[excited chatter]

271
00:12:08,916 --> 00:12:11,583
[RIMURU] I definitely
should have gone to that side.

272
00:12:11,666 --> 00:12:13,666
♪

273
00:12:15,291 --> 00:12:16,416
It's in here?

274
00:12:16,500 --> 00:12:17,791
[TEAR]
Sure is.

275
00:12:17,875 --> 00:12:19,708
[FOOTMAN]
It hasn't been revived yet,

276
00:12:19,791 --> 00:12:23,083
but can't you feel its thirst
for destruction pouring out?

277
00:12:23,166 --> 00:12:26,833
Such emotions make for
the most tantalizing treats.

278
00:12:26,916 --> 00:12:29,625
Hence how we were able
to find it.

279
00:12:29,708 --> 00:12:31,500
Yeah, you're right.

280
00:12:31,583 --> 00:12:33,625
There's an ominous feeling
in the air.

281
00:12:35,666 --> 00:12:37,041
Charybdis.

282
00:12:40,250 --> 00:12:42,250
[FOOTMAN]
Under normal circumstances,

283
00:12:42,333 --> 00:12:45,333
reviving Charybdis
would require many corpses.

284
00:12:45,416 --> 00:12:46,666
Corpses?

285
00:12:46,750 --> 00:12:48,125
[FOOTMAN] Right, you see
it's really more of

286
00:12:48,208 --> 00:12:49,875
a spiritual life form.

287
00:12:49,958 --> 00:12:52,333
In order to utilize its power
in this world,

288
00:12:52,416 --> 00:12:56,333
someone has to provide it
with a physical body to inhabit.

289
00:12:56,416 --> 00:12:58,375
I get that. So what?

290
00:12:58,458 --> 00:13:01,166
You haven't realized
your role yet?

291
00:13:03,416 --> 00:13:04,791
Hold on.

292
00:13:04,875 --> 00:13:05,916
You mean...

293
00:13:06,000 --> 00:13:07,791
[FOOTMAN]
When we say "subdue,"

294
00:13:07,875 --> 00:13:09,208
what we really mean

295
00:13:09,291 --> 00:13:11,708
is you have to take
Charybdis into your body.

296
00:13:11,791 --> 00:13:15,791
Then you'll merge together
into one all-powerful being!

297
00:13:15,875 --> 00:13:17,333
Are you serious?

298
00:13:18,333 --> 00:13:20,458
[TEAR]
It's not too late to turn back.

299
00:13:20,541 --> 00:13:22,375
-But...
-Spit it out.

300
00:13:22,458 --> 00:13:25,958
[TEAR] I'm not sure the seal
can hold out for much longer.

301
00:13:27,208 --> 00:13:29,291
And if it doesn't? Then what?

302
00:13:29,375 --> 00:13:33,041
[TEAR] It would find a way
to revive on its own, I guess.

303
00:13:33,125 --> 00:13:34,958
[PHOBIO] But you just said
it needs corpses.

304
00:13:35,041 --> 00:13:36,500
[TEAR]
Yes, true!

305
00:13:36,583 --> 00:13:38,041
But I'm sure
it's more than capable

306
00:13:38,125 --> 00:13:39,625
of acquiring the corpses
it needs

307
00:13:39,708 --> 00:13:41,083
for revival all by itself,

308
00:13:41,166 --> 00:13:42,416
with or without our help.

309
00:13:42,500 --> 00:13:43,958
And in that case,

310
00:13:44,041 --> 00:13:46,166
us and everyone around us
will be doomed.

311
00:13:46,250 --> 00:13:47,791
[FOOTMAN]
How right you are.

312
00:13:47,875 --> 00:13:50,125
[TEAR] If it manages
to revive on its own,

313
00:13:50,208 --> 00:13:51,708
it'll be uncontrollable.

314
00:13:51,791 --> 00:13:54,083
And since it won't have
a living vessel to guide it,

315
00:13:54,166 --> 00:13:56,833
then it will surely
do whatever it wants.

316
00:13:57,958 --> 00:14:00,625
[PHOBIO] So you're saying
we need to break the seal

317
00:14:00,708 --> 00:14:03,166
and take its power
before it can wake up?

318
00:14:03,250 --> 00:14:05,416
[TEAR]
Huh? Well, yeah.

319
00:14:05,500 --> 00:14:06,750
That should do the trick.

320
00:14:06,833 --> 00:14:08,291
[FOOTMAN]
Very perceptive.

321
00:14:08,375 --> 00:14:10,083
Fine then.

322
00:14:10,166 --> 00:14:13,750
I'm going to break the seal
and make its power my own.

323
00:14:15,250 --> 00:14:16,958
[footsteps]

324
00:14:22,125 --> 00:14:23,541
Charybdis.

325
00:14:23,625 --> 00:14:25,291
I'll do it.

326
00:14:25,375 --> 00:14:26,958
I'll subdue it with my own body.

327
00:14:28,083 --> 00:14:31,458
And then I'll get my revenge
on Demon Lord Milim.

328
00:14:35,833 --> 00:14:37,500
[FOOTMAN]
He actually went in.

329
00:14:37,583 --> 00:14:38,958
[TEAR]
He sure did.

330
00:14:39,041 --> 00:14:41,041
[FOOTMAN] That's a minion
of Lord Carrion for you,

331
00:14:41,125 --> 00:14:43,083
all muscle and no brain.

332
00:14:43,166 --> 00:14:44,875
[TEAR]
Makes things easier for us.

333
00:14:44,958 --> 00:14:46,833
[BOTH cackling]

334
00:14:47,833 --> 00:14:49,583
[FOOTMAN] Does that mean
the task is finished?

335
00:14:49,666 --> 00:14:51,291
[TEAR]
I think so.

336
00:14:51,375 --> 00:14:53,791
All Lord Clayman told me
was to revive Charybdis

337
00:14:53,875 --> 00:14:56,041
and send it towards Milim.

338
00:14:56,125 --> 00:14:57,583
-Hey.
-[FOOTMAN] Ooh?

339
00:14:57,666 --> 00:15:00,000
[TEAR] I left Lesser Dragon
corpses here earlier,

340
00:15:00,083 --> 00:15:01,666
but now they've disappeared.

341
00:15:01,750 --> 00:15:04,250
[FOOTMAN] Oh, well, so long
as we're prepared,

342
00:15:04,333 --> 00:15:06,083
there's nothing to worry about.

343
00:15:06,166 --> 00:15:08,083
[BOTH cackling]

344
00:15:12,583 --> 00:15:15,875
[groans]
It's so heavy.

345
00:15:15,958 --> 00:15:19,750
[laughing]
Pretty impressive haul, huh?

346
00:15:19,833 --> 00:15:20,916
[RIMURU]
Uh-huh.

347
00:15:21,000 --> 00:15:23,583
Lady Milim is just amazing.

348
00:15:23,666 --> 00:15:25,750
She's able to locate monsters
right away.

349
00:15:25,833 --> 00:15:28,166
It actually makes hunting them
pretty easy.

350
00:15:28,250 --> 00:15:29,583
[MILIM laughs]

351
00:15:29,666 --> 00:15:31,541
Finding monsters is simple
when you're amazing.

352
00:15:31,625 --> 00:15:33,666
We're gonna feast again tonight.

353
00:15:33,750 --> 00:15:35,125
[RIMURU]
Good job.

354
00:15:35,208 --> 00:15:36,625
Excellent work, everyone.

355
00:15:36,708 --> 00:15:38,791
Work's definitely a way
to describe it.

356
00:15:38,875 --> 00:15:41,291
Who wants to get a drink
and a bath?

357
00:15:41,375 --> 00:15:43,000
I'd love a drink.

358
00:15:43,083 --> 00:15:44,166
[laughs]

359
00:15:44,250 --> 00:15:45,583
[BOTH gasp]

360
00:15:45,666 --> 00:15:47,958
-[SHION] Lady Milim.
-[MILIM gasps]

361
00:15:48,041 --> 00:15:49,333
Who goes there?

362
00:15:49,416 --> 00:15:50,916
-[MILIM] Hmph.
-[RIMURU] Careful!

363
00:15:51,000 --> 00:15:51,958
Whoa, I've got you.

364
00:15:52,041 --> 00:15:53,333
[RIMURU]
This presence!

365
00:15:56,500 --> 00:15:58,666
♪

366
00:16:00,291 --> 00:16:01,625
[RIMURU]
It's Treyni.

367
00:16:01,708 --> 00:16:03,875
No, wait, she seems different.

368
00:16:03,958 --> 00:16:06,250
Huh? It's a dryad!

369
00:16:06,333 --> 00:16:08,166
Well, this is a first.

370
00:16:09,750 --> 00:16:12,708
Hello, there.
I am the Dryad Trya.

371
00:16:12,791 --> 00:16:14,250
Treyni's younger sister.

372
00:16:14,333 --> 00:16:15,916
[RIMURU]
Treyni's little sis?!

373
00:16:16,000 --> 00:16:18,708
Uh, wait, what's up
with the ominous aura

374
00:16:18,791 --> 00:16:19,750
you're emanating?

375
00:16:19,833 --> 00:16:22,583
An emergency has arisen.

376
00:16:22,666 --> 00:16:24,666
Calamity approaches us all.

377
00:16:24,750 --> 00:16:26,500
[RIMURU]
Like, how so?

378
00:16:26,583 --> 00:16:30,250
A calamity-class monster
Charybdis has been revived.

379
00:16:30,333 --> 00:16:31,791
[RIMURU]
Charyb-what?

380
00:16:34,125 --> 00:16:37,166
[TRYA] Its violence equals
that of a Demon Lord.

381
00:16:37,250 --> 00:16:38,916
My sisters, including Treyni,

382
00:16:39,000 --> 00:16:41,333
have set out
to slow its progress,

383
00:16:41,416 --> 00:16:43,500
but they aren't
strong enough.

384
00:16:43,583 --> 00:16:44,916
There's more.

385
00:16:45,000 --> 00:16:47,041
Judging by the monster's path,

386
00:16:47,125 --> 00:16:48,458
it's heading for this town.

387
00:16:48,541 --> 00:16:50,250
[ALL gasp]

388
00:16:51,916 --> 00:16:55,083
Against Charybdis, who's known
as the Ruler of the Skies,

389
00:16:55,166 --> 00:16:57,833
waging a war on land is futile.

390
00:16:57,916 --> 00:17:00,500
I've come to warn you
about your defenses.

391
00:17:00,583 --> 00:17:02,750
Form an airborne combat force.

392
00:17:02,833 --> 00:17:04,458
There isn't much time left.

393
00:17:07,791 --> 00:17:09,208
[TRYA]
The monster known as Charybdis

394
00:17:09,291 --> 00:17:10,500
was born a long time ago.

395
00:17:10,583 --> 00:17:13,833
And has died
and been revived many times.

396
00:17:13,916 --> 00:17:16,208
It is the violent
Ruler of the Skies.

397
00:17:16,291 --> 00:17:20,291
However, based on its lineage,
that's to be expected.

398
00:17:20,375 --> 00:17:23,750
It hails from Veldora,
the guardian of the forest.

399
00:17:23,833 --> 00:17:25,750
[RIMURU]
Like it's Veldora's child?

400
00:17:25,833 --> 00:17:27,958
[TRYA]
Yes, in a way.

401
00:17:28,041 --> 00:17:29,500
You see Charybdis was generated

402
00:17:29,583 --> 00:17:31,750
from a cloud
of Veldora's magicules.

403
00:17:32,875 --> 00:17:34,583
[RIMURU] So does that mean
the fish thing and I

404
00:17:34,666 --> 00:17:36,250
are kind of like siblings?

405
00:17:37,333 --> 00:17:38,750
Wait.

406
00:17:38,833 --> 00:17:41,291
I wonder if that's why
it's heading to our village.

407
00:17:41,375 --> 00:17:45,625
Maybe it knows that I've got
Veldora stashed in my stomach.

408
00:17:45,708 --> 00:17:48,041
If Charybdis has truly revived,

409
00:17:48,125 --> 00:17:50,833
then it's far more dangerous
than a Demon Lord.

410
00:17:50,916 --> 00:17:52,791
Because unlike most enemies,

411
00:17:52,875 --> 00:17:55,166
we have no way of speaking
with this opponent.

412
00:17:55,250 --> 00:17:57,916
True, it's a monster
with zero intelligence.

413
00:17:58,000 --> 00:18:01,500
It's said to have the ability to
summon floating shark creatures,

414
00:18:01,583 --> 00:18:04,166
known as Megalodons, who then
come from the spirit world

415
00:18:04,250 --> 00:18:06,083
to join it in its rampage.

416
00:18:06,166 --> 00:18:07,583
So I've heard, anyway.

417
00:18:07,666 --> 00:18:09,291
[RIMURU]
Man, for real?

418
00:18:09,375 --> 00:18:11,583
And I thought the Orc Lord
was bad.

419
00:18:11,666 --> 00:18:13,958
To make things even worse,

420
00:18:14,041 --> 00:18:16,208
the Megalodons
that it's summoned,

421
00:18:16,291 --> 00:18:17,791
well, it looks like
they've possessed

422
00:18:17,875 --> 00:18:20,333
some Lesser Dragon corpses
that happened to be nearby.

423
00:18:20,416 --> 00:18:21,375
[RIMURU]
What?

424
00:18:21,458 --> 00:18:23,791
[TRYA]
There are 13 of them.

425
00:18:23,875 --> 00:18:26,333
[RIMURU] Great, so there's
a fish as strong as Demon Lord,

426
00:18:26,416 --> 00:18:28,875
and 13 shark lackeys
following it.

427
00:18:28,958 --> 00:18:31,958
Easy-peasy lemon squeezy.

428
00:18:32,041 --> 00:18:34,333
Lord Rimuru,
what should we do?

429
00:18:34,416 --> 00:18:36,250
[RIMURU]
I'm not sure yet.

430
00:18:36,333 --> 00:18:38,000
-[MILIM snickers]
-[RIMURU] Huh?

431
00:18:38,083 --> 00:18:41,291
Come on, are you sure you're not
forgetting someone important?

432
00:18:41,375 --> 00:18:43,583
That stupid fish...

433
00:18:43,666 --> 00:18:46,291
is no match for a Demon Lord.

434
00:18:46,375 --> 00:18:47,916
I'll obliterate Charybdis.

435
00:18:48,000 --> 00:18:49,625
[RIMURU] Hell, yeah!
Why didn't I think of that?

436
00:18:49,708 --> 00:18:51,500
I'm sorry, but we can't
allow you to.

437
00:18:51,583 --> 00:18:52,875
[MILIM gasps]

438
00:18:52,958 --> 00:18:54,791
This is our town,
and therefore our problem.

439
00:18:54,875 --> 00:18:56,916
[RIMURU] But it doesn't
have to be just our problem!

440
00:18:57,000 --> 00:18:58,458
Huh? Really?

441
00:18:58,541 --> 00:18:59,666
But I'm his bestie.

442
00:18:59,750 --> 00:19:01,208
Shion's right.

443
00:19:01,291 --> 00:19:02,875
We can't rely on you
for everything

444
00:19:02,958 --> 00:19:04,250
just because
you're our friend.

445
00:19:04,333 --> 00:19:07,500
When Lord Rimuru is in
desperate need of help,

446
00:19:07,583 --> 00:19:10,583
when he's out of options,
we'll call on you, Lady Milim.

447
00:19:10,666 --> 00:19:11,916
[RIMURU]
I'm feeling pretty desperate

448
00:19:12,000 --> 00:19:13,333
right now, though.

449
00:19:13,416 --> 00:19:15,291
-[RIMURU chuckles nervously]
-[MILIM groaning]

450
00:19:15,375 --> 00:19:16,625
[RIMURU]
They're right, Milim.

451
00:19:16,708 --> 00:19:18,458
Just have faith in me.

452
00:19:18,541 --> 00:19:19,708
[groans]

453
00:19:19,791 --> 00:19:22,041
But I... I thought...

454
00:19:22,125 --> 00:19:25,250
I'd finally get my chance
to shine a little, you know?

455
00:19:25,333 --> 00:19:27,958
[RIMURU]
I guess Charybdis is after me.

456
00:19:28,041 --> 00:19:30,416
So it's not fair
to rely on Milim.

457
00:19:30,500 --> 00:19:32,375
-[MILIM groaning]
-[RIMURU] Hmm!

458
00:19:32,458 --> 00:19:35,375
Begin preparations
to defeat Charybdis.

459
00:19:35,458 --> 00:19:36,625
[ALL]
Right.

460
00:19:36,708 --> 00:19:38,708
[MILIM]
This whole thing is so unfair.

461
00:19:38,791 --> 00:19:40,875
Beat Charybdis?

462
00:19:40,958 --> 00:19:43,833
Listen, this won't be easy.

463
00:19:43,916 --> 00:19:46,666
Not even the dryads
can take this monster down.

464
00:19:46,750 --> 00:19:47,791
You know that, right?

465
00:19:48,833 --> 00:19:50,000
[RIMURU]
Thanks to the treaty,

466
00:19:50,083 --> 00:19:52,291
we can count on King Gazel
for back up.

467
00:19:52,375 --> 00:19:53,791
We'll just have to do our best.

468
00:19:54,833 --> 00:19:56,916
Why not just run away?

469
00:19:57,000 --> 00:19:58,541
[RIMURU]
What good would that do?

470
00:19:58,625 --> 00:20:01,333
Look, I'm the strongest guy
in this nation.

471
00:20:02,833 --> 00:20:04,458
If things start to look
really bad,

472
00:20:04,541 --> 00:20:06,500
then I'll bail
and think up a new plan.

473
00:20:06,583 --> 00:20:09,916
But in the meantime, I should
at least face this thing head-on

474
00:20:10,000 --> 00:20:11,916
and see how
strong it is, right?

475
00:20:14,166 --> 00:20:15,541
Yes, perhaps.

476
00:20:15,625 --> 00:20:17,083
I mean, you are the leader.

477
00:20:17,166 --> 00:20:18,666
It makes sense.

478
00:20:18,750 --> 00:20:20,166
[RIMURU]
We're different from humans,

479
00:20:20,250 --> 00:20:21,333
you guys are done for

480
00:20:21,416 --> 00:20:22,875
if something happens
to your king.

481
00:20:23,875 --> 00:20:25,416
[FUZE]
Well, that may be the case,

482
00:20:25,500 --> 00:20:28,000
but one thing I've noticed
about you these past few days

483
00:20:28,083 --> 00:20:30,375
is that you reason
much like a human.

484
00:20:30,458 --> 00:20:32,750
It's kind of hard to think
of you as a monster.

485
00:20:32,833 --> 00:20:34,125
[RIMURU]
Hmm.

486
00:20:34,208 --> 00:20:36,083
You may be on to something.

487
00:20:36,166 --> 00:20:39,000
This might be tough to believe,
but once upon a time,

488
00:20:39,083 --> 00:20:40,791
I actually used
to be a human.

489
00:20:40,875 --> 00:20:43,291
You know about Shizu, right?

490
00:20:43,375 --> 00:20:45,666
I'm pretty sure
I'm an otherworlder,

491
00:20:45,750 --> 00:20:47,041
just like she was.

492
00:20:47,125 --> 00:20:49,000
I died in my world.

493
00:20:51,875 --> 00:20:54,916
And then, I was reincarnated
here as a slime.

494
00:20:55,000 --> 00:20:56,416
[FUZE gasping]

495
00:20:56,500 --> 00:20:57,791
You're like Shizu?

496
00:20:59,625 --> 00:21:01,500
She and I are
from the same place.

497
00:21:01,583 --> 00:21:04,500
That's why she entrusted
everything to me.

498
00:21:04,583 --> 00:21:06,125
I gained this human form

499
00:21:06,208 --> 00:21:08,250
in exchange
for inheriting her will.

500
00:21:11,250 --> 00:21:13,583
And I can't exactly go around
making dumb mistakes

501
00:21:13,666 --> 00:21:15,500
while I look like Shizu.

502
00:21:15,583 --> 00:21:16,916
I see.

503
00:21:17,000 --> 00:21:18,250
